This is a SQLite extension that provides a few file management SQL functions:

	FILE_MKDIR(PATHNAME)
	FILE_TO_FILE(SOURCEPATHNAME, DESTINATIONPATHNAME)
	
	BLOB_CRC32(BLOBCONTENT)
	FILE_CRC32(PATHNAME)
	
	FILE_DATE_MODIFIED(PATHNAME)
	FILE_SIZE(PATHNAME)
	FILE_EXISTS(PATHNAME)
	
	FILE_EXTENSION(PATHNAME)
	FILE_FILENAME(PATHNAME)
	FILE_BASENAME(PATHNAME)
	FILE_UPDIR(PATHNAME)

See test/test002-basic.sql and test/test003-write.sql for a few usage examples.

### How to compile

	make all

### How to run the test suite

After the extension and the test program have been compiled with "make all", type "make check".
The test suite has been confirmed to pass on MinGW64 in Windows.
